1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 24=

3
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:49,130
Thank you.

4
00:01:58,130 --> 00:01:58,850
Hello.

5
00:01:58,850 --> 00:02:00,020
Are you Mr. Shen?

6
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:01,330
Yes.

7
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:03,690
Hello, I'm the agent.

8
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:04,410
Hello.

9
00:02:04,410 --> 00:02:05,620
Good timing. Let's head up.

10
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:06,460
- It's just upstairs.
- Let's go.

11
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:07,330
After you.

12
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:08,820
It's quite lively down here.

13
00:02:08,820 --> 00:02:10,060
Yeah, pretty lively.

14
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:10,940
Come.

15
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:12,100
Mr. Shen,

16
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,890
to be honest, around here,

17
00:02:13,890 --> 00:02:15,170
it's mostly '80s and '90s

18
00:02:15,170 --> 00:02:16,410
High Court staff housing,

19
00:02:16,410 --> 00:02:17,730
basically all older public units.

20
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:19,780
I prefer living closer to work.

21
00:02:19,866 --> 00:02:21,500
Alright, let's take a look at this one.

22
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:22,540
This way.

23
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,540
Come in.

24
00:02:26,380 --> 00:02:27,380
Do I need shoe covers?

25
00:02:27,850 --> 00:02:28,410
No.

26
00:02:28,410 --> 00:02:30,660
I'll mop the floor later.

27
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:31,660
It's fine.

28
00:02:33,850 --> 00:02:34,610
Mr. Shen,

29
00:02:34,730 --> 00:02:36,220
actually, this unit

30
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:37,340
hasn't been officially

31
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:38,850
listed in our system yet.

32
00:02:38,850 --> 00:02:40,010
I thought I'd show you first.

33
00:02:40,890 --> 00:02:43,220
The previous owner lived here,

34
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:44,410
the renovation is decent.

35
00:02:44,410 --> 00:02:45,170
Take a look.

36
00:02:45,170 --> 00:02:46,660
It's been well kept.

37
00:02:47,170 --> 00:02:48,260
Do I pay rent quarterly?

38
00:02:48,570 --> 00:02:52,500
♪Happy birthday to you♪

39
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:57,170
♪Happy birthday to you♪

40
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,820
Happy birthday.

41
00:02:58,820 --> 00:02:59,660
Have a seat.

42
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:01,130
Let them enjoy it first.

43
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:02,100
Alright.

44
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:05,340
Sit.

45
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:06,130
Thank you.

46
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:07,340
Have some water.

47
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:11,010
It's the kid's birthday today?

48
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:12,940
Yes, it's his birthday.

49
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,170
What happened to him today?

50
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,500
He ran off in such a hurry.

51
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:17,010
I noticed his hands,

52
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:19,100
looked like there were old injuries.

53
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:20,780
He was abused as a child.

54
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:23,380
His arms are covered in cigarette burns.

55
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:25,450
Is he an orphan?

56
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:27,570
No, it was his own family who did it.

57
00:03:27,820 --> 00:03:28,980
Hard to imagine, right?

58
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:30,660
He's been with us for a few months now.

59
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:32,780
He had basically recovered,

60
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:34,290
but since it's his birthday today,

61
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:36,450
we got him a cake

62
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:37,690
and lit some candles.

63
00:03:37,890 --> 00:03:39,010
Because of the burns,

64
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,170
he has a stress reaction to flames.

65
00:03:41,730 --> 00:03:43,450
That was our oversight.

66
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:47,130
Are you alright?
I'm really sorry about that.

67
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:48,130
I'm fine.

68
00:03:49,540 --> 00:03:50,410
It's just

69
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:51,730
hard to imagine a child

70
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:54,170
so young has gone through so much.

71
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:55,890
Some people are born into comfort,

72
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:57,540
others are born into hardship.

73
00:03:57,690 --> 00:03:59,010
What can we really do?

74
00:03:59,340 --> 00:04:00,380
All we can do

75
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:02,410
is try our best to help them.

76
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:04,890
To be honest,

77
00:04:05,170 --> 00:04:06,980
I don't know much about legal aid,

78
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,380
but since I'm here,

79
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:09,780
I do want to help.

80
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:12,850
If there's anything I can do,

81
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:14,260
just let me know.

82
00:04:14,380 --> 00:04:15,500
That's great.

83
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:16,490
How about this?

84
00:04:16,610 --> 00:04:17,850
This Friday,

85
00:04:18,020 --> 00:04:20,370
we have a joint
anti-domestic violence meeting.

86
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:21,730
Come with me,

87
00:04:21,730 --> 00:04:22,900
just get a feel for it.

88
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:24,730
Friday? Where?

89
00:04:25,410 --> 00:04:26,900
At Qingcheng Court.

90
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:31,140
Is that a problem?

91
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:34,370
I'm just worried

92
00:04:34,930 --> 00:04:36,580
I might not finish my cases by then.

93
00:04:38,490 --> 00:04:40,100
How about this? Reach out to me then.

94
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:41,850
If I can make it,

95
00:04:42,170 --> 00:04:43,250
I'll let you know.

96
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:44,100
Alright.

97
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,050
Then

98
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,250
I'll reserve you a spot.

99
00:04:47,490 --> 00:04:48,730
I'll contact you then.

100
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:51,410
I really hope you can make it.

101
00:05:22,644 --> 00:05:24,250
Where are we going for supper later?

102
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:25,340
Why are you here?

103
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:27,020
Weren't we supposed

104
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:28,290
to meet at the restaurant?

105
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:30,340
Then let's go eat.

106
00:05:30,490 --> 00:05:33,200
I'm already here, can't you
at least let me have a sip of water?

107
00:05:33,290 --> 00:05:34,370
What's the rush?

108
00:05:36,930 --> 00:05:38,250
This little place of yours,

109
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,690
even though
you haven't lived in it,

110
00:05:39,711 --> 00:05:40,730
now that you're moving out,

111
00:05:40,755 --> 00:05:41,900
I kind of hate to see it go.

112
00:05:41,930 --> 00:05:43,540
Well, out with the old, in with the new.

113
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:44,370
Yeah.

114
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:47,580
So how's the house hunt going?

115
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:49,466
Places near
the High Court are expensive.

116
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,610
Yeah, they are.

117
00:05:51,644 --> 00:05:52,730
But I've already found one.

118
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:54,050
You found one?

119
00:05:54,930 --> 00:05:55,900
Let's go, time to eat.

120
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,290
I've already decided what I want.

121
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:57,730
Let's go.

122
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:59,980
What's the rush? Can't I sit for a bit?

123
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:00,900
You really...

124
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:03,700
What's this?

125
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,020
These are specialties
from Qin Rui's hometown.

126
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:20,050
You've kept them all this time?

127
00:06:21,730 --> 00:06:22,580
Look at this.

128
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:24,220
They're so hard
they could be used as a weapon.

129
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,666
I'll throw them out for you later.

130
00:06:25,688 --> 00:06:26,460
Don't touch them.

131
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:28,540
What's wrong?

132
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:31,290
You're not even
in a relationship with Qin Rui.

133
00:06:32,022 --> 00:06:33,622
There's nothing between you,

134
00:06:33,755 --> 00:06:35,410
so why are you still so hung up on it?

135
00:06:35,410 --> 00:06:36,660
You think I'm like you?

136
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:38,100
Just forget whenever I feel like it?

137
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:38,930
Heartless.

138
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:44,050
Fine. If that's how you see it,
I have nothing to say.

139
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:45,844
I don't feel like staying here anymore.

140
00:06:45,911 --> 00:06:46,580
I'm leaving.

141
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:51,540
Weren't we going for supper?

142
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:52,490
Not anymore.

143
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:54,900
It's a long night, you can stay here

144
00:06:55,155 --> 00:06:57,088
and nurse your broken heart alone.

145
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:21,610
Who's that?

146
00:07:22,730 --> 00:07:26,660
He looks like he's
from Chenxi Legal Aid Center.

147
00:07:31,488 --> 00:07:33,490
These are specialties
from Qin Rui's hometown.

148
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:37,050
You've kept them all this time.

149
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:56,460
(Lou Yue)

150
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:05,780
(Can you do me a favor?)

151
00:08:09,260 --> 00:08:13,100
(Can you do me a favor?)

152
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,460
You're back.

153
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:27,850
Carrying so many books again.

154
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:29,370
Can you even finish them?

155
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:32,610
At least I can understand them now.

156
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:35,340
That wasn't easy.

157
00:08:36,133 --> 00:08:37,700
I think you're really getting the hang

158
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:39,700
of non-litigation work now.

159
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:43,130
I went to the Legal Aid Center today

160
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:44,490
to take a look in person.

161
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:45,940
The Legal Aid Center?

162
00:08:48,530 --> 00:08:49,650
How was it?

163
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,700
I think

164
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:54,650
it was pretty good.

165
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:56,770
Today I saw

166
00:08:56,770 --> 00:08:58,180
someone helping a woman

167
00:08:58,180 --> 00:08:59,730
who wanted a divorce

168
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:01,060
draft her complaint.

169
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:02,580
And others

170
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:04,890
helping children who were abused,

171
00:09:05,060 --> 00:09:06,180
comforting them.

172
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,220
There was also someone

173
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,850
handling a 24-hour suicide hotline.

174
00:09:11,850 --> 00:09:12,530
The reason I want

175
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:13,980
to go to the Legal Aid Center

176
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,530
is because recently,

177
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,340
after working on non-litigation

178
00:09:18,490 --> 00:09:19,890
and economic cases,

179
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:22,300
I feel like I really need to think about

180
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:24,730
why I wanted to become
a lawyer in the first place.

181
00:09:27,850 --> 00:09:29,580
I remember when I was little,

182
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:31,730
I used to watch legal dramas a lot,

183
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:33,530
and I imagined scenes like that,

184
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:36,180
helping people

185
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:37,730
who truly need help,

186
00:09:37,888 --> 00:09:39,622
being there for them
when it matters most,

187
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:41,820
helping those in the dark

188
00:09:42,130 --> 00:09:43,220
find their way out.

189
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:46,650
So today,

190
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,130
I actually gained quite a lot.

191
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:52,340
But hearing you say that,

192
00:09:52,511 --> 00:09:53,890
are you starting to feel tempted?

193
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Feeling it isn't enough,
you have to act.

194
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,610
With where I am right now,

195
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:02,010
to be honest,
the Legal Aid Center doesn't pay much,

196
00:10:02,355 --> 00:10:03,777
how am I supposed to manage?

197
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,610
But

198
00:10:06,730 --> 00:10:08,300
if I can grow

199
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:09,730
my video channel

200
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:11,530
and build a more stable following,

201
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:13,850
and if real cases start coming in,

202
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:16,100
and people are willing
to pay me for consultations,

203
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:17,980
then maybe I really could

204
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:19,180
make both sides work.

205
00:10:20,650 --> 00:10:22,220
You definitely can.

206
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:29,700
♪Become your soaring wings♪

207
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:38,540
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

208
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:42,350
♪I want to be in your world♪

209
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:46,100
(Don't overthink it.)

210
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:48,100
(Time to move on.)

211
00:10:52,830 --> 00:10:56,620
♪I want to be in your world♪

212
00:10:56,620 --> 00:11:00,160
♪I'll be your shelter♪

213
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:06,170
♪I'll be there
for you until the very end♪

214
00:11:06,580 --> 00:11:07,580
Long time no see.

215
00:11:08,980 --> 00:11:09,980
Long time no see.

216
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,650
(What are they talking about?)

217
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,610
(Why are they standing so close?)

218
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:34,730
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

219
00:11:35,890 --> 00:11:38,060
(Why were we so naive back then?)

220
00:11:40,460 --> 00:11:42,850
(A moment worth celebrating.)

221
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:45,700
(He apologized to me today, everyone.)

222
00:11:45,755 --> 00:11:47,150
(Come on, let's get a better angle.)

223
00:11:47,177 --> 00:11:48,220
(Let's take another selfie.)

224
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:50,300
(Friends and family, bear witness.)

225
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:51,370
(This is Judge Shen Xiezhi.)

226
00:11:51,370 --> 00:11:53,060
(Today I didn't go looking for him,)

227
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:54,610
(he's the one who came up to me.)

228
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:55,980
(I'm recording this as proof.)

229
00:11:55,980 --> 00:11:56,820
(I testify to that.)

230
00:11:56,820 --> 00:12:01,700
♪I'll be there for you
until the very end♪

231
00:12:01,730 --> 00:12:02,820
(Shen Xiezhi,)

232
00:12:03,850 --> 00:12:05,100
(have you lost your mind?)

233
00:12:09,060 --> 00:12:10,580
(See? That's proof.)

234
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:17,190
♪You are the only one that I see♪

235
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:21,200
♪I want to be in your world♪

236
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,020
♪Everything is no longer faraway♪

237
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:27,180
(Ronghe Law Firm)

238
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:42,660
(Phase One: Asset-Backed Note Issuance)

239
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:52,660
(Senior Partner)

240
00:12:58,844 --> 00:13:01,100
Ms. Lou, I'll go over
these materials one more time,

241
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,370
then I can hand them to you.

242
00:13:02,370 --> 00:13:04,180
No rush, I need you for something else.

243
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:04,850
About that,

244
00:13:04,850 --> 00:13:07,100
the judgment
for the Jiang Cheng case is out.

245
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:08,650
Go to Qingcheng Court tomorrow

246
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:09,610
and pick it up.

247
00:13:10,850 --> 00:13:12,010
Qingcheng Court?

248
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:16,580
Isn't that Mu's case?

249
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:19,266
Her eyes aren't feeling well,
she took the day off tomorrow.

250
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:21,340
The main thing is,

251
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:23,610
I still haven't finished
what I'm working on.

252
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:25,180
Qingcheng Court,

253
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,610
you're the most familiar with it.

254
00:13:27,311 --> 00:13:28,370
It's just a small errand,

255
00:13:28,370 --> 00:13:29,530
stop passing it around.

256
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,111
Go first thing tomorrow morning.

257
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:35,220
Morning, Ms. Lou.

258
00:13:45,422 --> 00:13:47,155
(It's the last day)
(His last day)

259
00:13:47,155 --> 00:13:49,150
(before transferring to the High Court.)

260
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:52,610
Sir,

261
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:53,940
where are Yuanbao and madam?

262
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:57,340
His mom took him to ride the bus.

263
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,490
Yuanbao likes taking the bus.

264
00:13:59,730 --> 00:14:00,890
Don't let his looks fool you,

265
00:14:01,622 --> 00:14:03,820
which stop to get off,
which route to transfer,

266
00:14:03,977 --> 00:14:05,090
he knows it better than I do.

267
00:14:05,370 --> 00:14:06,300
Then...

268
00:14:07,130 --> 00:14:08,700
About things between you and madam...

269
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:09,940
I don't resent her anymore.

270
00:14:10,730 --> 00:14:11,730
Back then,

271
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,370
my family wronged her too.

272
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:15,059
It's also my fault
for not being capable,

273
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:16,010
not making enough money,

274
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:18,530
that's why everything
that followed happened.

275
00:14:20,180 --> 00:14:21,100
Now,

276
00:14:21,155 --> 00:14:22,980
I just want this settled
as soon as possible.

277
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,300
When is the hearing?

278
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,100
She said...

279
00:14:26,622 --> 00:14:28,000
I don't want to hear what she says.

280
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:29,730
Whatever she says,
I don't want to hear it.

281
00:14:29,890 --> 00:14:31,890
Just seeing her makes me uncomfortable.

282
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:34,770
I don't want to see her.

283
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:35,980
She said

284
00:14:36,460 --> 00:14:37,610
she agreed to the divorce.

285
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,420
At least she has some conscience,

286
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,370
willing to let me go.

287
00:14:49,511 --> 00:14:51,155
Then let's just
get the hearing scheduled.

288
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,590
The sooner it's settled,
the sooner it's over.

289
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:54,890
As for the property...

290
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:56,100
I don't want it.

291
00:14:56,250 --> 00:14:57,580
I don't want it.

292
00:14:57,610 --> 00:14:58,980
I don't want anything.

293
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:00,610
All I want is my pension.

294
00:15:01,490 --> 00:15:02,610
I'll leave with nothing.

295
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:08,300
She also said

296
00:15:09,060 --> 00:15:11,010
she and Yuanbao will leave with nothing.

297
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:15,340
That old woman...

298
00:15:15,730 --> 00:15:17,340
Isn't this just putting me on the spot?

299
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:18,940
She thinks

300
00:15:18,940 --> 00:15:20,610
I can't bear to see the two of them

301
00:15:20,890 --> 00:15:21,980
end up on the street.

302
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:23,220
Tell her this,

303
00:15:23,530 --> 00:15:24,530
even if she does that,

304
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:25,770
I won't change my mind.

305
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:27,420
Dad!

306
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:29,940
Dad!

307
00:15:34,580 --> 00:15:35,580
You're back.

308
00:15:35,820 --> 00:15:36,770
Dad!

309
00:15:36,770 --> 00:15:37,700
Candied hawthorn.

310
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:38,490
I don't want any.

311
00:15:38,490 --> 00:15:39,370
Candied hawthorn!

312
00:15:39,555 --> 00:15:40,060
It's good.

313
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:41,370
You eat it, I don't want it.

314
00:15:41,370 --> 00:15:43,530
Yuanbao, it's time
for your dad to take his medicine.

315
00:15:48,850 --> 00:15:49,730
Here.

316
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,530
Careful, it's hot.

317
00:15:56,970 --> 00:15:58,955
Take your medicine,
then have the candied hawthorn.

318
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:01,490
Didn't I tell you? I don't want it.

319
00:16:05,730 --> 00:16:06,610
Yuanbao,

320
00:16:06,610 --> 00:16:07,850
come on, let's go over there.

321
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:09,755
Don't interrupt your dad
while he's talking.

322
00:16:10,580 --> 00:16:11,370
Let's go.

323
00:16:12,610 --> 00:16:13,490
Let's go.

324
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:21,650
Just rule it the way I said.

325
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:23,300
I'm leaving.

326
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:25,850
Without me,
they'll still manage just fine.

327
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:28,730
I'm leaving.

328
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,180
What do we do now?

329
00:16:30,340 --> 00:16:32,010
I thought there might
be a turning point.

330
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:36,490
They've been together for so many years,

331
00:16:36,890 --> 00:16:37,530
I just feel

332
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:39,580
Mr. Wang can't let this go,

333
00:16:39,777 --> 00:16:41,250
it's not that he has no feelings left

334
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:43,250
for Yuanbao and Madam Qiu.

335
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:45,530
Have you ever seen anyone

336
00:16:45,530 --> 00:16:47,250
insisting on leaving with nothing?

337
00:16:49,490 --> 00:16:50,580
I just think

338
00:16:51,111 --> 00:16:52,370
we shouldn't give up on this

339
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:54,370
so easily.

340
00:16:55,133 --> 00:16:56,130
Let's wait and see.

341
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:58,370
Maybe before the hearing,
he'll change his mind.

342
00:16:58,700 --> 00:16:59,610
Judge Shen.

343
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,340
- Judge Shen.
- Sir.

344
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:03,980
Yuanbao was right there just now,

345
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,290
I couldn't speak freely.

346
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:07,050
I just got him to sleep.

347
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:08,530
I only want to say,

348
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,140
staying in this family

349
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:13,530
for even one more day is torture.

350
00:17:14,180 --> 00:17:15,490
Whenever you hold the hearing,

351
00:17:16,090 --> 00:17:17,180
just issue the ruling.

352
00:17:18,010 --> 00:17:19,220
If this keeps dragging on,

353
00:17:19,460 --> 00:17:20,620
I might as well end it.

354
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,010
Sir, please don't say that.

355
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:26,700
I promise you,

356
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:27,940
we won't mediate anymore.

357
00:17:28,222 --> 00:17:30,288
We'll proceed to the hearing
as soon as possible.

358
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:32,250
Alright.

359
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:41,460
(Article 4, Article 5)

360
00:17:43,290 --> 00:17:44,420
Still working?

361
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:45,420
Have you eaten?

362
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:48,220
Didn't get the chance.

363
00:17:49,140 --> 00:17:50,660
Come on, I'll take you out.

364
00:17:50,860 --> 00:17:53,010
That barbecue place downstairs
smells amazing.

365
00:17:53,460 --> 00:17:54,490
Come on, let's go.

366
00:17:54,980 --> 00:17:55,900
You coming or not?

367
00:17:58,490 --> 00:17:59,090
I can't.

368
00:17:59,090 --> 00:18:01,530
I need to finish this

369
00:18:01,530 --> 00:18:02,460
and send it to Ms. Lou.

370
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:03,460
(New articles
of association and capital...)

371
00:18:03,570 --> 00:18:04,980
Work is important,

372
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:06,180
but you can't skip meals.

373
00:18:07,570 --> 00:18:08,420
How about tomorrow?

374
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:09,730
I'll treat you to something good.

375
00:18:10,050 --> 00:18:11,050
You said it.

376
00:18:11,460 --> 00:18:12,010
Then tomorrow,

377
00:18:12,010 --> 00:18:14,290
I'll be working near your office.

378
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:15,466
I'll come find you at noon,

379
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:16,770
and we'll have pizza.

380
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:19,860
Tomorrow...

381
00:18:19,860 --> 00:18:21,220
Tomorrow might not work.

382
00:18:22,530 --> 00:18:24,050
I need to go to Qingcheng Court.

383
00:18:24,050 --> 00:18:25,460
Qingcheng Court?

384
00:18:25,955 --> 00:18:28,490
You're not appearing in court,
so what are you going there for?

385
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:30,220
Jiang Cheng, the celebrity case,

386
00:18:30,220 --> 00:18:31,250
it's my colleague's.

387
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,888
They asked me to go pick something up.

388
00:18:33,220 --> 00:18:35,660
Why would your colleague's case
need you to pick it up?

389
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:36,900
I don't know.

390
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:39,010
My boss told me to go,
so I can't just refuse, right?

391
00:18:42,140 --> 00:18:43,730
Tomorrow,

392
00:18:43,770 --> 00:18:45,090
isn't it Shen Xiezhi's

393
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:46,660
last day in Qingcheng?

394
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:51,330
I knew something was up.

395
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:54,330
What do you mean something's up?

396
00:18:54,420 --> 00:18:55,700
That case isn't his,

397
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:57,250
it's Judge Yu's.

398
00:18:58,180 --> 00:18:59,050
Judge Yu

399
00:18:59,050 --> 00:19:00,810
shares an office with him, okay?

400
00:19:00,810 --> 00:19:01,900
Come on.

401
00:19:02,220 --> 00:19:03,900
Really... That has nothing
to do with you.

402
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:05,888
Why would they
specifically ask you to go?

403
00:19:06,090 --> 00:19:07,010
Besides,

404
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:08,250
the judgment...

405
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:10,290
One day earlier or later doesn't matter.

406
00:19:10,770 --> 00:19:12,090
Why does it have to be that day?

407
00:19:13,288 --> 00:19:14,940
There's definitely something going on.

408
00:19:15,022 --> 00:19:16,760
Do you think
she's trying to set you two up?

409
00:19:17,220 --> 00:19:19,490
Set us up?
Ms. Lou is busy enough as it is.

410
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:21,220
Who has time to worry about us?

411
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:23,180
Besides, between me and Shen Xiezhi,

412
00:19:23,180 --> 00:19:25,377
is he going to give up
his job at the High Court,

413
00:19:25,444 --> 00:19:27,140
or am I going to give up mine at Ronghe?

414
00:19:28,180 --> 00:19:29,980
Go take care of your own business.

415
00:19:29,980 --> 00:19:31,380
Go on, go.

416
00:19:35,890 --> 00:19:39,080
♪Turn around for every part of life♪

417
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:43,140
♪Rushing between buildings♪

418
00:19:45,377 --> 00:19:46,980
Everything will go smoothly today.

419
00:19:47,740 --> 00:19:51,490
♪Facing the surging waves of life♪

420
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:55,440
♪Hearing the ticking
of a wound-up spring♪

421
00:19:55,460 --> 00:19:56,380
Morning, Judge Shen.

422
00:19:56,380 --> 00:19:57,290
Morning, Mr. Wang.

423
00:19:57,290 --> 00:20:01,300
♪Ready to chase dreams
through sleepless nights♪

424
00:20:02,420 --> 00:20:03,250
Ms. Qin,

425
00:20:03,311 --> 00:20:04,700
Judge Yu asked me to come get you.

426
00:20:04,940 --> 00:20:05,570
Alright.

427
00:20:05,810 --> 00:20:06,730
Let's head inside.

428
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:07,860
Thanks.

429
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:10,090
Ms. Qin, this way.

430
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:14,560
♪I will step into the crowd♪

431
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:18,570
Le, Ms. Qin is here.

432
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:21,770
You're here.

433
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:22,900
Judge Yu.

434
00:20:23,140 --> 00:20:26,380
(Courtroom 6, available)

435
00:20:27,911 --> 00:20:29,530
Judge Shen, you were looking for me?

436
00:20:30,770 --> 00:20:31,700
Close the door.

437
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:37,530
Judge Shen,

438
00:20:37,810 --> 00:20:38,940
what is this about?

439
00:20:40,244 --> 00:20:42,330
When you go into court later,
wear a bit less,

440
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:47,380
and get yourself some water.

441
00:20:51,570 --> 00:20:52,660
Go back to your seat,

442
00:20:52,711 --> 00:20:53,860
pretend to type for a bit.

443
00:21:08,490 --> 00:21:09,330
Okay.

444
00:21:09,555 --> 00:21:11,490
Let's run through
this afternoon's hearing.

445
00:21:11,490 --> 00:21:12,250
A run-through?

446
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:14,180
Of the hearing?

447
00:21:14,550 --> 00:21:16,155
Did you bring the authorization letter?

448
00:21:16,220 --> 00:21:17,220
Yes.

449
00:21:19,330 --> 00:21:20,250
Here it is.

450
00:21:23,380 --> 00:21:24,140
Alright.

451
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:25,770
This is the judgment.

452
00:21:26,050 --> 00:21:27,570
If everything looks correct,

453
00:21:27,730 --> 00:21:29,620
(Case: Divorce Dispute)
please sign the receipt.

454
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:31,730
Okay.

455
00:21:32,740 --> 00:21:35,220
(Service recipient signature
or seal: Qin Rui)

456
00:21:36,050 --> 00:21:36,980
Alright, thank you.

457
00:21:36,980 --> 00:21:37,810
Okay.

458
00:21:39,220 --> 00:21:40,380
See you.

459
00:21:40,460 --> 00:21:41,250
See you.

460
00:22:03,311 --> 00:22:04,420
What are you doing here?

461
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:08,180
I came to pick up a judgment.

462
00:22:12,050 --> 00:22:12,980
Got it?

463
00:22:17,730 --> 00:22:18,620
You...

464
00:22:21,490 --> 00:22:22,620
I'm about to go into court.

465
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:28,220
This case is a bit complicated.

466
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:31,220
Alright.

467
00:22:31,570 --> 00:22:32,900
Then go ahead,

468
00:22:33,140 --> 00:22:34,220
don't let me hold you up.

469
00:22:57,220 --> 00:22:59,810
Ms. Lou, I've picked up the judgment.

470
00:22:59,810 --> 00:23:00,810
I'll bring it to you now.

471
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:02,140
Did you see Judge Shen?

472
00:23:02,140 --> 00:23:04,330
I did, just said hello.

473
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:05,940
What did you talk about?

474
00:23:06,140 --> 00:23:07,180
Nothing really.

475
00:23:07,180 --> 00:23:08,900
I was in a hurry to bring this to you.

476
00:23:09,570 --> 00:23:11,010
You're in a hurry,

477
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:12,570
but this can wait a bit.

478
00:23:13,380 --> 00:23:14,620
Go back for me.

479
00:23:16,570 --> 00:23:17,490
Go back?

480
00:23:18,380 --> 00:23:19,810
Ask Shen Xiezhi

481
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:21,940
when he's returning

482
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:22,980
my copy of Jinji Cong.

483
00:23:24,220 --> 00:23:26,980
Jinji Cong? What's that?

484
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:29,900
You studied law, didn't you?

485
00:23:30,380 --> 00:23:31,940
Lu Ailin's collection of speeches,

486
00:23:32,380 --> 00:23:33,530
you don't know it?

487
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:35,860
Sounds familiar.

488
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:38,530
Then...

489
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:40,700
What should I do now?

490
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:43,050
Go back and ask Shen Xiezhi

491
00:23:44,250 --> 00:23:46,090
when he's returning my book.

492
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:47,660
He's had it for ten years.

493
00:23:47,810 --> 00:23:48,810
Ten years?

494
00:23:50,420 --> 00:23:52,010
This old debt...

495
00:23:52,490 --> 00:23:54,180
What's wrong with an old debt?

496
00:23:54,420 --> 00:23:56,700
I just want to get back
the reason I became a lawyer.

497
00:23:57,010 --> 00:23:58,490
If you can't even get a book back,

498
00:23:58,570 --> 00:24:00,200
how are you going to handle major cases?

499
00:24:00,290 --> 00:24:02,010
Who says I can't get it back?

500
00:24:06,660 --> 00:24:08,740
(High People's Court)

501
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:13,780
(Jiang Feng)

502
00:24:18,530 --> 00:24:19,160
Hello?

503
00:24:19,450 --> 00:24:20,180
Hello?

504
00:24:21,330 --> 00:24:23,140
Finished the call?

505
00:24:23,290 --> 00:24:24,220
Yeah.

506
00:24:24,330 --> 00:24:25,490
I told her to go back again.

507
00:24:26,810 --> 00:24:28,050
I've done all I can.

508
00:24:28,380 --> 00:24:30,530
If the two of them
still can't sort things out,

509
00:24:30,733 --> 00:24:32,250
you should just give up on this idea.

510
00:24:32,860 --> 00:24:33,770
Alright.

511
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:35,490
I'll never

512
00:24:35,570 --> 00:24:36,810
forget this favor.

513
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:38,530
Cut it out.

514
00:24:39,220 --> 00:24:40,620
You and Shen Xiezhi,

515
00:24:41,330 --> 00:24:42,730
between the two of you,

516
00:24:43,090 --> 00:24:44,380
neither can repay me anyway.

517
00:24:44,700 --> 00:24:46,770
Just consider it
my good deed for the day.

518
00:24:47,570 --> 00:24:48,980
Alright, thanks.

519
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:02,500
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

520
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,140
You're still here?

521
00:25:14,730 --> 00:25:16,490
Ms. Lou just called me,

522
00:25:16,980 --> 00:25:18,330
said she wanted something from you.

523
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:19,770
Do you remember?

524
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:22,050
She said she lent you a book.

525
00:25:22,900 --> 00:25:23,810
The Thorn Birds...

526
00:25:25,730 --> 00:25:28,250
No, Jinji Cong.

527
00:25:28,420 --> 00:25:29,460
That book,

528
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:31,090
she wants it back?

529
00:25:31,860 --> 00:25:32,770
Probably

530
00:25:32,770 --> 00:25:35,570
trying to reconnect
with why she became a lawyer.

531
00:25:38,730 --> 00:25:40,050
That book is at my place.

532
00:25:40,290 --> 00:25:41,460
I'll mail it to her later.

533
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,140
Alright.

534
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:48,460
Thanks for the trouble.

535
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,660
Qin Rui.

536
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:01,090
Judge Shen, I was just looking for you.

537
00:26:01,244 --> 00:26:02,490
The parties will be here soon,

538
00:26:02,490 --> 00:26:03,490
I'm still a bit nervous.

539
00:26:03,490 --> 00:26:05,180
How about we
run through it one more time?

540
00:26:05,570 --> 00:26:06,460
Ms. Qin.

541
00:26:07,180 --> 00:26:08,180
A run-through?

542
00:26:08,490 --> 00:26:10,660
Judge Shen's last case
before going to the High Court,

543
00:26:10,660 --> 00:26:13,570
we'll definitely treat it with full
seriousness and close it perfectly,

544
00:26:13,570 --> 00:26:15,490
so he can leave

545
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:16,460
without any regrets.

546
00:26:16,460 --> 00:26:17,660
You're the one leaving.

547
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:19,090
What I mean is,

548
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:20,860
wrap up this chapter properly,

549
00:26:20,940 --> 00:26:22,220
and start a new one in life.

550
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:23,090
That's what I meant.

551
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:24,140
Alright, got it.

552
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:26,111
You go ahead first,
I'll come find you in a bit.

553
00:26:26,140 --> 00:26:27,090
Okay.

554
00:26:33,066 --> 00:26:34,940
What were you
about to say to me just now?

555
00:26:42,980 --> 00:26:43,980
Take care.

556
00:27:03,940 --> 00:27:05,010
Stop working already.

557
00:27:05,330 --> 00:27:06,420
We're heading out.

558
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:07,940
Okay.

559
00:27:12,730 --> 00:27:14,940
Hurry up, I'll wait for you outside.

560
00:27:16,660 --> 00:27:17,530
Dad.

561
00:27:17,980 --> 00:27:18,900
Let's go out and play.

562
00:27:20,422 --> 00:27:21,250
Let's go out and play.

563
00:27:21,380 --> 00:27:23,180
Yuanbao, I'm going out
with your mom for a bit.

564
00:27:23,250 --> 00:27:24,250
We'll be back soon.

565
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:26,220
Together.

566
00:27:26,220 --> 00:27:27,220
Yeah.

567
00:27:27,420 --> 00:27:28,900
We'll be back soon.

568
00:27:29,420 --> 00:27:30,380
Together.

569
00:27:31,460 --> 00:27:33,010
Yuanbao, you're not going.

570
00:27:33,460 --> 00:27:34,810
Come, let mom tell you something.

571
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:35,460
Come here.

572
00:27:35,530 --> 00:27:36,380
Go on.

573
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:38,180
Come.

574
00:27:42,330 --> 00:27:43,220
Hurry up.

575
00:27:47,620 --> 00:27:49,220
Alright, I know.

576
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:51,860
Come here.

577
00:27:52,570 --> 00:27:53,420
Okay.

578
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:55,770
Sit down.

579
00:27:56,570 --> 00:27:57,460
Quick.

580
00:27:59,050 --> 00:28:00,010
Alright.

581
00:28:00,088 --> 00:28:02,000
We'll take you out later
when we're back.

582
00:28:05,010 --> 00:28:07,090
Come on, take off your clothes.

583
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:14,220
Take off your shoes yourself.

584
00:28:19,010 --> 00:28:19,940
Yuanbao,

585
00:28:20,250 --> 00:28:21,570
mom will give you some candy.

586
00:28:23,050 --> 00:28:24,460
After that, we'll go to sleep.

587
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:27,250
Open your mouth.

588
00:28:31,660 --> 00:28:32,570
Water.

589
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:38,940
Get on the bed.

590
00:28:40,420 --> 00:28:41,330
Come.

591
00:28:49,460 --> 00:28:50,620
Good boy, Yuanbao.

592
00:28:51,220 --> 00:28:52,290
Close your eyes.

593
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:55,620
Mom and dad will be back soon.

594
00:29:15,260 --> 00:29:18,940
(Tianhai High-Tech Industrial
Development Zone People's Court)

595
00:29:58,080 --> 00:30:03,520
♪When a leaf can't find a place to fall♪

596
00:30:05,070 --> 00:30:06,660
♪Just like me♪

597
00:30:06,660 --> 00:30:09,880
♪Wandering without a destination♪

598
00:30:12,150 --> 00:30:17,740
♪Until you appear and I see your eyes♪

599
00:30:18,022 --> 00:30:20,090
(So there's really no chance
between you two anymore?)

600
00:30:22,180 --> 00:30:24,460
(None. Not even a little.)

601
00:30:26,940 --> 00:30:27,770
(But just now...)

602
00:30:27,770 --> 00:30:30,111
(You clearly still had something
you wanted to say to him.)

603
00:30:30,330 --> 00:30:31,980
(You obviously still like him.)

604
00:30:32,670 --> 00:30:36,480
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

605
00:30:36,490 --> 00:30:39,290
(But isn't being a lawyer your dream?)

606
00:30:39,570 --> 00:30:41,010
(Are you going to give that up?)

607
00:30:42,488 --> 00:30:44,860
(Haven't you already started
doing non-litigation work?)

608
00:30:45,010 --> 00:30:46,140
(No need to appear in court,)

609
00:30:46,140 --> 00:30:47,770
(then you could be with him, right?)

610
00:30:50,330 --> 00:30:51,460
(Non-litigation...)

611
00:30:51,570 --> 00:30:53,660
(I'm only just starting to take that on.)

612
00:30:53,860 --> 00:30:55,250
(It's not that simple.)

613
00:30:56,288 --> 00:30:58,180
(You've seen
how tough it's been lately.)

614
00:30:58,530 --> 00:30:59,810
(Haven't you?)

615
00:31:00,090 --> 00:31:03,050
(Then can you really bear
to give him up?)

616
00:31:06,380 --> 00:31:07,530
(No matter what,)

617
00:31:08,330 --> 00:31:10,380
(there are things
you have to say face to face.)

618
00:31:23,660 --> 00:31:24,700
Hello, Judge Shen.

619
00:31:24,900 --> 00:31:25,770
Hello.

620
00:31:28,610 --> 00:31:35,440
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

621
00:31:36,010 --> 00:31:39,620
♪I want to be in your world♪

622
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:43,240
♪And cast away my disguise♪

623
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:49,120
♪Lean on my tender shoulder♪

624
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:50,770
(How full of yourself.)

625
00:31:50,770 --> 00:31:52,330
(To think she was waiting for you.)

626
00:31:52,730 --> 00:31:54,380
(Why would she wait for you?)

627
00:32:08,220 --> 00:32:09,290
Judge Shen!

628
00:32:10,330 --> 00:32:11,490
Judge Shen!

629
00:32:13,010 --> 00:32:13,900
Slow down.

630
00:32:16,620 --> 00:32:17,380
Judge Shen.

631
00:32:17,530 --> 00:32:19,180
You even came down to meet us.

632
00:32:20,810 --> 00:32:22,460
I'll take you to the waiting area first.

633
00:32:22,660 --> 00:32:23,490
Alright.

634
00:32:23,770 --> 00:32:24,530
Let's go.

635
00:32:24,530 --> 00:32:25,380
Which way?

636
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:25,860
This way.

637
00:32:25,860 --> 00:32:26,700
Okay.

638
00:32:27,770 --> 00:32:30,330
Sorry to trouble you with our mess.

639
00:32:30,770 --> 00:32:31,810
It's my duty.

640
00:32:41,180 --> 00:32:42,050
Here,

641
00:32:44,050 --> 00:32:44,860
sir, madam,

642
00:32:45,010 --> 00:32:46,530
the previous hearing isn't over yet.

643
00:32:46,688 --> 00:32:48,140
Please have a seat here for a while.

644
00:32:48,250 --> 00:32:49,330
When it's about to start,

645
00:32:49,420 --> 00:32:50,730
someone will come call you.

646
00:32:51,460 --> 00:32:52,700
Thank you, Judge Shen.

647
00:32:53,220 --> 00:32:54,810
Go ahead if you're busy.

648
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:55,940
Thanks.

649
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:57,700
I'll go get ready then.

650
00:32:57,810 --> 00:32:58,530
Have a seat.

651
00:32:58,530 --> 00:32:59,250
Okay.

652
00:33:00,810 --> 00:33:01,660
That's fine.

653
00:33:14,530 --> 00:33:15,660
(Shen Xiezhi.)

654
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:17,220
(Do you have a moment later?)

655
00:33:18,860 --> 00:33:19,730
(No, wait...)

656
00:33:19,940 --> 00:33:22,010
(Judge Shen, do you
have a moment later?)

657
00:33:22,220 --> 00:33:24,420
(I'll be waiting
in the central courtyard.)

658
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:42,820
(Judge Shen, do you have a moment later?
I'll be waiting in the central courtyard.)

659
00:33:43,020 --> 00:33:45,940
(Courtroom 2 is in session)

660
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:49,940
(Under maintenance)

661
00:33:56,900 --> 00:33:59,090
Why are there
so many people today? It's so stuffy.

662
00:33:59,250 --> 00:34:00,530
I'll open a window.

663
00:34:00,530 --> 00:34:01,290
Okay.

664
00:34:10,820 --> 00:34:11,780
Young man.

665
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:13,980
Young man, close the window.

666
00:34:14,820 --> 00:34:15,650
Young...

667
00:34:15,940 --> 00:34:16,980
I'm not cold.

668
00:34:27,533 --> 00:34:29,090
How about we move over there instead?

669
00:34:29,210 --> 00:34:30,422
There's a seat over there.

670
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:33,460
Didn't I tell you? I'm not cold.

671
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:46,380
(Qingcheng District People's Court
Anti-Domestic Violence Joint Conference)

672
00:34:46,380 --> 00:34:47,980
(Oppose Domestic Violence)

673
00:34:48,980 --> 00:34:49,980
Ms. Qin,

674
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:52,460
are you still coming
to today's joint meeting?

675
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:53,650
What meeting?

676
00:34:54,555 --> 00:34:56,980
I told you before, the anti-domestic
violence joint meeting

677
00:34:56,980 --> 00:34:58,490
at Qingcheng Court.

678
00:35:01,690 --> 00:35:03,130
I... I completely forgot.

679
00:35:04,050 --> 00:35:06,050
But I happen to be
at Qingcheng Court right now.

680
00:35:06,130 --> 00:35:07,130
What time does it start?

681
00:35:07,210 --> 00:35:08,740
You're here? It's starting right away.

682
00:35:08,740 --> 00:35:09,900
I've saved you a seat.

683
00:35:10,300 --> 00:35:10,860
Okay.

684
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:11,940
Then I'll head over now.

685
00:35:11,940 --> 00:35:13,080
It's on the second floor, right?

686
00:35:13,090 --> 00:35:14,570
Yes, second-floor meeting room.

687
00:35:14,580 --> 00:35:15,733
Come on. We're waiting for you.

688
00:35:15,740 --> 00:35:17,210
Alright, I'm coming.

689
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:22,780
(Children's Room In Use)

690
00:35:23,490 --> 00:35:24,460
Look,

691
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:27,380
see what grandma bought for you.

692
00:35:27,940 --> 00:35:29,610
Here, little cheese.

693
00:35:30,650 --> 00:35:31,570
Cheese.

694
00:35:31,820 --> 00:35:33,170
And waffles.

695
00:35:33,740 --> 00:35:35,130
Here, Du, cake.

696
00:35:35,570 --> 00:35:36,490
Go on, eat.

697
00:35:41,860 --> 00:35:42,690
Alright then,

698
00:35:42,690 --> 00:35:44,780
grandma will leave the food here.

699
00:35:44,820 --> 00:35:47,260
Whenever you're hungry, just take some,

700
00:35:47,420 --> 00:35:48,260
okay?

701
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:54,900
Du,

702
00:35:55,170 --> 00:35:57,490
why are you looking at me like that?

703
00:35:57,780 --> 00:35:59,980
Like I'm your enemy.

704
00:36:01,090 --> 00:36:02,300
Let me tell you,

705
00:36:02,420 --> 00:36:03,980
it's not that I didn't want you.

706
00:36:04,530 --> 00:36:06,170
You were the one who told

707
00:36:06,170 --> 00:36:08,170
the judge in court
you wanted to go with your mom.

708
00:36:08,690 --> 00:36:10,380
If you're having second thoughts now,

709
00:36:10,530 --> 00:36:11,570
it's not too late.

710
00:36:11,690 --> 00:36:12,980
If you want to stay with grandma,

711
00:36:13,420 --> 00:36:13,860
then later,

712
00:36:13,860 --> 00:36:15,570
I can take you both with me.

713
00:36:15,650 --> 00:36:16,740
I'm staying with mom.

714
00:36:17,170 --> 00:36:18,210
Look at that,

715
00:36:18,210 --> 00:36:20,530
I loved you for nothing all those years.

716
00:36:22,490 --> 00:36:23,530
It's fine.

717
00:36:23,610 --> 00:36:25,460
As long as you
remember grandma's kindness.

718
00:36:26,130 --> 00:36:28,260
The judge might not even rule that way.

719
00:36:28,460 --> 00:36:30,260
That wouldn't be fair to your mom.

720
00:36:30,740 --> 00:36:32,780
Three children, and she gets none?

721
00:36:33,130 --> 00:36:35,170
She wouldn't be able to face anyone.

722
00:36:35,780 --> 00:36:36,740
Besides,

723
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:39,980
grandma isn't unreasonable.

724
00:36:41,610 --> 00:36:42,780
Here, have one. Eat.

725
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:43,780
Enough, mom.

726
00:36:44,010 --> 00:36:45,530
Out of the three kids, you want two.

727
00:36:45,820 --> 00:36:47,170
If it were me, I'd just take one.

728
00:36:47,530 --> 00:36:49,490
Isn't one enough to keep you company?

729
00:36:49,577 --> 00:36:50,940
Two together would just be trouble.

730
00:36:50,940 --> 00:36:52,300
Be quiet.

731
00:36:52,490 --> 00:36:55,170
If I had had one more child back then,

732
00:36:55,860 --> 00:36:56,820
I wouldn't have had to

733
00:36:56,820 --> 00:36:58,460
place all my hopes on you.

734
00:36:58,780 --> 00:36:59,650
Putting everything

735
00:36:59,650 --> 00:37:00,780
on you,

736
00:37:00,780 --> 00:37:02,650
what a loss that turned out to be.

737
00:37:02,650 --> 00:37:03,170
Alright,

738
00:37:03,170 --> 00:37:04,740
just pretend I didn't say anything.

739
00:37:05,010 --> 00:37:05,820
Honestly...

740
00:37:06,050 --> 00:37:08,210
You still have the nerve to say that.

741
00:37:14,570 --> 00:37:16,300
That's why grandma kept telling your mom

742
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:17,650
to have a couple more children.

743
00:37:17,820 --> 00:37:18,650
See?

744
00:37:18,940 --> 00:37:20,570
That's how you two came along.

745
00:37:21,420 --> 00:37:22,780
Meng and Bei,

746
00:37:23,490 --> 00:37:25,780
you should be thanking grandma.

747
00:37:25,860 --> 00:37:26,780
Right?

748
00:37:29,260 --> 00:37:30,130
Come.

749
00:37:35,380 --> 00:37:36,260
Judge Shen,

750
00:37:36,690 --> 00:37:37,650
it's time to go.

751
00:37:40,940 --> 00:37:41,980
All rise.

752
00:37:42,940 --> 00:37:45,820
Please welcome
the Presiding Judge and Panel Judges.

753
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:55,340
(Panel Judge)

754
00:37:56,210 --> 00:37:57,090
Please be seated.

755
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:03,133
Court is now in session.

756
00:38:03,380 --> 00:38:04,620
Your Honor,

757
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:06,740
I have new evidence to submit.

758
00:38:06,740 --> 00:38:08,111
(Panel Judge. Presiding Judge)

759
00:38:08,155 --> 00:38:10,620
(Defendant)

760
00:38:10,620 --> 00:38:11,900
(Employment Contract)

761
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:17,130
This is my payroll card

762
00:38:17,610 --> 00:38:18,690
and my service contract.

763
00:38:19,090 --> 00:38:20,650
I want to show the court

764
00:38:21,170 --> 00:38:22,460
that I am fully capable

765
00:38:22,460 --> 00:38:24,090
of supporting my own child.

766
00:38:27,690 --> 00:38:29,170
Let's not go over the past.

767
00:38:29,170 --> 00:38:30,780
(Family Court)

768
00:38:30,780 --> 00:38:32,460
There's no real dispute
over our property,

769
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:33,911
so let's just move things along.

770
00:38:33,980 --> 00:38:35,260
Sir, that won't work.

771
00:38:35,570 --> 00:38:37,530
Neither you nor madam wants the house,

772
00:38:38,050 --> 00:38:39,130
that's still an issue.

773
00:38:39,300 --> 00:38:41,010
No matter who it ends up going to,

774
00:38:41,380 --> 00:38:43,380
we need a clear resolution, right?

775
00:38:44,210 --> 00:38:45,610
What resolution do we need?

776
00:38:45,940 --> 00:38:47,780
I can sleep anywhere.

777
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:50,010
But she's an old woman
with a troubled son.

778
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:52,090
If they end up out on the street,

779
00:38:52,170 --> 00:38:53,130
and a car honks,

780
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,822
he has another episode
and hurts someone,

781
00:38:54,860 --> 00:38:56,210
who takes responsibility?

782
00:38:56,860 --> 00:38:58,980
I can't deal with that anymore.

783
00:39:00,130 --> 00:39:01,130
You don't have to.

784
00:39:01,690 --> 00:39:03,050
Easy for you to say.

785
00:39:03,980 --> 00:39:04,860
If I don't,

786
00:39:05,420 --> 00:39:07,740
all these years, every time
he caused trouble outside,

787
00:39:07,780 --> 00:39:10,130
who was the one apologizing

788
00:39:10,340 --> 00:39:11,380
and paying compensation?

789
00:39:11,420 --> 00:39:14,170
Well, you say I don't
have to deal with it.

790
00:39:14,260 --> 00:39:16,340
But will the neighbors see it that way?

791
00:39:18,860 --> 00:39:20,900
If I give you the house,
it's not because

792
00:39:20,980 --> 00:39:22,780
I still have feelings for you,

793
00:39:23,780 --> 00:39:25,300
I just want some peace.

794
00:39:26,650 --> 00:39:28,260
Just take it.

795
00:39:28,340 --> 00:39:29,300
I don't want it.

796
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:35,822
Are you trying to drag me down with you?

797
00:39:40,820 --> 00:39:41,610
Sir,

798
00:39:41,980 --> 00:39:43,050
please calm down.

799
00:39:43,380 --> 00:39:45,010
Your concerns

800
00:39:45,010 --> 00:39:46,490
are actually unnecessary.

801
00:39:46,690 --> 00:39:48,210
After your divorce,

802
00:39:48,380 --> 00:39:50,650
custody of Wang Yuanbao
will go to madam.

803
00:39:51,260 --> 00:39:52,340
Any legal consequences

804
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:54,170
arising from his actions

805
00:39:54,260 --> 00:39:56,460
will also be borne by her alone.

806
00:39:56,860 --> 00:39:58,980
If anyone comes to you
for compensation later,

807
00:39:59,380 --> 00:40:00,530
you can refuse.

808
00:40:01,490 --> 00:40:02,380
Yes.

809
00:40:02,690 --> 00:40:04,530
It feels a bit warm in here,

810
00:40:04,900 --> 00:40:06,420
could we lower the temperature?

811
00:40:06,690 --> 00:40:07,570
Sure.

812
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:11,340
(Temperature)

813
00:40:11,340 --> 00:40:13,740
(Defendant)

814
00:40:16,530 --> 00:40:17,420
I don't need any.

815
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:29,980
Before marriage,

816
00:40:29,980 --> 00:40:32,300
I worked for this media company,

817
00:40:32,650 --> 00:40:33,650
contributing articles.

818
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:35,650
Now that my boss heard I'm coming back,

819
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:37,210
he's very happy.

820
00:40:37,210 --> 00:40:39,610
This job doesn't
require me to be on-site.

821
00:40:39,610 --> 00:40:41,088
(Defendant)
I only need to go in

822
00:40:41,088 --> 00:40:42,010
once a week for meetings.

823
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:43,420
If I'm really busy,

824
00:40:43,780 --> 00:40:44,740
I can just communicate

825
00:40:44,780 --> 00:40:46,610
with my boss online.

826
00:40:46,690 --> 00:40:47,740
Although

827
00:40:47,860 --> 00:40:50,210
my current salary isn't very high,

828
00:40:50,380 --> 00:40:52,780
around six thousand a month,

829
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:54,900
it gives me enough time

830
00:40:55,130 --> 00:40:56,300
to take care of my children.

831
00:40:56,420 --> 00:40:57,820
And with my abilities, I believe...

832
00:40:57,820 --> 00:40:59,050
Alright, that's enough.

833
00:40:59,460 --> 00:41:00,380
Stop right there.

834
00:41:02,090 --> 00:41:03,300
Back when you

835
00:41:03,380 --> 00:41:05,900
weren't working, you barely managed

836
00:41:05,940 --> 00:41:07,980
to take care of the kids.

837
00:41:07,980 --> 00:41:08,900
How?

838
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:11,690
Now you want to work and take care
of them at the same time?

839
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:14,900
What if you fail at both

840
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:16,530
and end up neglecting the children?

841
00:41:17,820 --> 00:41:19,570
Your Honor, I have a suggestion.

842
00:41:19,820 --> 00:41:22,260
If all the children are awarded to me,

843
00:41:22,260 --> 00:41:23,130
I have the means

844
00:41:23,130 --> 00:41:24,780
to hire multiple nannies

845
00:41:24,780 --> 00:41:26,460
and a private tutor.

846
00:41:26,820 --> 00:41:27,740
Then

847
00:41:27,740 --> 00:41:29,260
Shi Xiaomei can work

848
00:41:29,260 --> 00:41:30,380
however she wants.

849
00:41:30,488 --> 00:41:31,333
Is that acceptable?

850
00:41:31,377 --> 00:41:32,200
Your Honor,

851
00:41:32,380 --> 00:41:33,820
my eldest daughter, Du

852
00:41:34,010 --> 00:41:35,210
is very sensible.

853
00:41:35,340 --> 00:41:36,210
After school,

854
00:41:36,210 --> 00:41:37,977
she can help me
take care of the younger ones.

855
00:41:37,980 --> 00:41:40,170
And Du has excellent grades,

856
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:42,090
helping with their homework

857
00:41:42,130 --> 00:41:43,460
won't be a problem.

858
00:41:43,610 --> 00:41:45,010
Now my mother has also agreed

859
00:41:45,210 --> 00:41:46,311
she can come by often

860
00:41:46,377 --> 00:41:47,820
to help take care of the children.

861
00:41:47,820 --> 00:41:48,780
Enough.

862
00:41:48,980 --> 00:41:50,610
Stop bringing up your mother.

863
00:41:51,170 --> 00:41:53,010
Someone like her,

864
00:41:53,090 --> 00:41:54,380
why didn't she come earlier?

865
00:41:55,980 --> 00:41:57,900
Now that I've raised the kids,

866
00:41:57,900 --> 00:41:59,130
she suddenly wants to step in?

867
00:41:59,210 --> 00:42:01,170
My mom never said she wouldn't come.

868
00:42:01,170 --> 00:42:02,300
Don't forget,

869
00:42:02,690 --> 00:42:04,420
you were the one who drove her away.

870
00:42:04,420 --> 00:42:05,380
Alright.

871
00:42:05,980 --> 00:42:07,130
What is this...

872
00:42:07,530 --> 00:42:08,260
Fine.

873
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:10,010
Now you've got a job,

874
00:42:10,111 --> 00:42:11,844
so you think you've got what it takes,

875
00:42:12,010 --> 00:42:13,980
and your mom can help you now.

876
00:42:14,170 --> 00:42:15,170
That's fine.

877
00:42:15,740 --> 00:42:16,570
Your Honor,

878
00:42:16,690 --> 00:42:19,380
our financial situations

879
00:42:19,530 --> 00:42:20,740
are clear.

880
00:42:20,740 --> 00:42:23,860
If Meng and Bei are awarded to me,

881
00:42:24,900 --> 00:42:26,300
she won't have to pay a cent,

882
00:42:26,690 --> 00:42:29,170
and I'll still pay Du's support.

883
00:42:29,170 --> 00:42:31,260
But if all three children go to her,

884
00:42:31,460 --> 00:42:32,650
I won't pay anything.

885
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:35,460
She can go ask their father for money.

886
00:42:40,644 --> 00:42:42,444
The plaintiff
requests that the defendant

887
00:42:42,577 --> 00:42:45,260
repay all child support for Wang Yuanbao

888
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:47,420
from birth until now,

889
00:42:47,460 --> 00:42:49,780
a total of 1,387,000 yuan.

890
00:42:49,980 --> 00:42:51,260
Forget it.

891
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:52,380
Sir,

892
00:42:52,555 --> 00:42:54,444
do you confirm
you are giving up this claim?

893
00:42:54,460 --> 00:42:55,300
Yes.

894
00:42:55,570 --> 00:42:56,460
Your reason?

895
00:42:56,533 --> 00:42:58,511
If I'm giving it up,
what reason do I need?

896
00:42:58,800 --> 00:42:59,940
I need to confirm with you

897
00:42:59,940 --> 00:43:00,780
that you understand

898
00:43:00,780 --> 00:43:02,570
the consequences of this decision,

899
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:04,010
to avoid future disputes.

900
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

901
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

902
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

903
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

904
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

905
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

906
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

907
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

908
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

909
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

910
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

911
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

912
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

913
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

914
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

915
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

916
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

917
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

918
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

919
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

920
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

921
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

922
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

923
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

924
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

925
